{"kind": "callout", "id": "105d05a1c83ac4bc", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#overview", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "The CLI was previously called \"headless mode.\" The `-p` flag and all CLI options work the same way."}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "e6b133ac8ac44d4b", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#overview", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Find and fix the bug in auth.py\" --allowedTools \"Read,Edit,Bash\"", "preceding_paragraph": "To run Claude Code programmatically from the CLI, pass `-p` with your prompt and any CLI options:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Use the Agent SDK to run Claude Code programmatically from the CLI, Python, or TypeScript.\n\nThe Agent SDK gives you the same tools, agent loop, and context management that power Claude Code. It's available as a CLI for scripts and CI/CD, or as Python and TypeScript packages for full programmatic control.\n\nTo run Claude Code programmatically from the CLI, pass `-p` with your prompt and any CLI options:\n\nThis page covers using the Agent SDK via the CLI (`claude -p`). For the Python and TypeScript SDK packages with structured outputs, tool approval callbacks, and native message objects, see the full Agent SDK documentation.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "af68c49234fc2bce", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#basic-usage", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"What does the auth module do?\"", "preceding_paragraph": "This example asks Claude a question about your codebase and prints the response:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "fac992038349d23f", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#start-faster-with-bare-mode", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude --bare -p \"Summarize this file\" --allowedTools \"Read\"", "preceding_paragraph": "This example runs a one-off summarize task in bare mode and pre-approves the Read tool so the call completes without a permission prompt:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
