{"kind": "callout", "id": "553388693e8bbdd8", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#start-faster-with-bare-mode", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "`--bare` is the recommended mode for scripted and SDK calls, and will become the default for `-p` in a future release."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#start-faster-with-bare-mode", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "start-faster-with-bare-mode", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Basic usage > Start faster with bare mode", "level": 3, "position": 2, "text": "Add `--bare` to reduce startup time by skipping auto-discovery of hooks, skills, plugins, MCP servers, auto memory, and CLAUDE.md. Without it, `claude -p` loads the same context an interactive session would, including anything configured in the working directory or `~/.claude`.\n\nBare mode is useful for CI and scripts where you need the same result on every machine. A hook in a teammate's `~/.claude` or an MCP server in the project's `.mcp.json` won't run, because bare mode never reads them. Only flags you pass explicitly take effect.\n\nThis example runs a one-off summarize task in bare mode and pre-approves the Read tool so the call completes without a permission prompt:\n\nIn bare mode Claude has access to the Bash, file read, and file edit tools. Pass any context you need with a flag:\n\nBare mode skips OAuth and keychain reads. Anthropic authentication must come from `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` or an `apiKeyHelper` in the JSON passed to `--settings`. Bedrock, Vertex, and Foundry use their usual provider credentials.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#basic-usage", "external_links": ["http://CLAUDE.md"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#basic-usage", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "basic-usage", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Basic usage", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "Add the `-p` (or `--print`) flag to any `claude` command to run it non-interactively. All CLI options work with `-p`, including:\n\n- `--continue` for continuing conversations\n- `--allowedTools` for auto-approving tools\n- `--output-format` for structured output\n\nThis example asks Claude a question about your codebase and prints the response:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "9cd7784438de9b1c", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#get-structured-output", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Summarize this project\" --output-format json", "preceding_paragraph": "This example returns a project summary as JSON with session metadata, with the text result in the `result` field:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7b50018ea5e32b4e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#get-structured-output", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Extract the main function names from auth.py\" \\\n  --output-format json \\\n  --json-schema '{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"functions\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"}}},\"required\":[\"functions\"]}'", "preceding_paragraph": "This example extracts function names and returns them as an array of strings:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "6776951a684dfde3", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#get-structured-output", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "tip", "text": "Use a tool like jq to parse the response and extract specific fields:"}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#get-structured-output", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "get-structured-output", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Get structured output", "level": 3, "position": 4, "text": "Use `--output-format` to control how responses are returned:\n\n- `text` (default): plain text output\n- `json`: structured JSON with result, session ID, and metadata\n- `stream-json`: newline-delimited JSON for real-time streaming\n\nThis example returns a project summary as JSON with session metadata, with the text result in the `result` field:\n\nTo get output conforming to a specific schema, use `--output-format json` with `--json-schema` and a JSON Schema definition. The response includes metadata about the request (session ID, usage, etc.) with the structured output in the `structured_output` field.\n\nThis example extracts function names and returns them as an array of strings:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": ["https://jqlang.github.io/jq/", "https://json-schema.org/"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "a45cfaaf9b993d89", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#stream-responses", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Explain recursion\" --output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages", "preceding_paragraph": "Use `--output-format stream-json` with `--verbose` and `--include-partial-messages` to receive tokens as they're generated. Each line is a JSON object representing an event:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "5c8c785a17f0835e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#stream-responses", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Write a poem\" --output-format stream-json --verbose --include-partial-messages | \\\n  jq -rj 'select(.type == \"stream_event\" and .event.delta.type? == \"text_delta\") | .event.delta.text'", "preceding_paragraph": "The following example uses jq to filter for text deltas and display just the streaming text. The `-r` flag outputs raw strings (no quotes) and `-j` joins without newlines so tokens stream continuously:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
