{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "412c6f95b33341a1", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#stream-responses", "position": 6, "table_position": 2, "headers": ["field", "type", "description"], "cells": ["`session_id`", "string", "session the event belongs to"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#stream-responses", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "stream-responses", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Stream responses", "level": 3, "position": 5, "text": "Use `--output-format stream-json` with `--verbose` and `--include-partial-messages` to receive tokens as they're generated. Each line is a JSON object representing an event:\n\nThe following example uses jq to filter for text deltas and display just the streaming text. The `-r` flag outputs raw strings (no quotes) and `-j` joins without newlines so tokens stream continuously:\n\nWhen an API request fails with a retryable error, Claude Code emits a `system/api_retry` event before retrying. You can use this to surface retry progress or implement custom backoff logic.\n\nThe `system/init` event reports session metadata including the model, tools, MCP servers, and loaded plugins. It is the first event in the stream unless `CLAUDE_CODE_SYNC_PLUGIN_INSTALL` is set, in which case `plugin_install` events precede it. Use the plugin fields to fail CI when a plugin did not load:\n\nWhen `CLAUDE_CODE_SYNC_PLUGIN_INSTALL` is set, Claude Code emits `system/plugin_install` events while marketplace plugins install before the first turn. Use these to surface install progress in your own UI.\n\nFor programmatic streaming with callbacks and message objects, see Stream responses in real-time in the Agent SDK documentation.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": ["https://jqlang.github.io/jq/"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "84a3995d16fb7591", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#auto-approve-tools", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Run the test suite and fix any failures\" \\\n  --allowedTools \"Bash,Read,Edit\"", "preceding_paragraph": "Use `--allowedTools` to let Claude use certain tools without prompting. This example runs a test suite and fixes failures, allowing Claude to execute Bash commands and read/edit files without asking for permission:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "2e34f3f82752b2fa", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#auto-approve-tools", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Apply the lint fixes\" --permission-mode acceptEdits", "preceding_paragraph": "To set a baseline for the whole session instead of listing individual tools, pass a permission mode. `dontAsk` denies anything not in your `permissions.allow` rules or the read-only command set, which is useful for locked-down CI runs. `acceptEdits` lets Claude write files without prompting and also auto-approves common filesystem commands such as `mkdir`, `touch`, `mv`, and `cp`. Other shell commands and network requests still need an `--allowedTools` entry or a `permissions.allow` rule, otherwise the run aborts when one is attempted:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#auto-approve-tools", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "auto-approve-tools", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Auto-approve tools", "level": 3, "position": 6, "text": "Use `--allowedTools` to let Claude use certain tools without prompting. This example runs a test suite and fixes failures, allowing Claude to execute Bash commands and read/edit files without asking for permission:\n\nTo set a baseline for the whole session instead of listing individual tools, pass a permission mode. `dontAsk` denies anything not in your `permissions.allow` rules or the read-only command set, which is useful for locked-down CI runs. `acceptEdits` lets Claude write files without prompting and also auto-approves common filesystem commands such as `mkdir`, `touch`, `mv`, and `cp`. Other shell commands and network requests still need an `--allowedTools` entry or a `permissions.allow` rule, otherwise the run aborts when one is attempted:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7f73479c6d0d73f3", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#create-a-commit", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "claude -p \"Look at my staged changes and create an appropriate commit\" \\\n  --allowedTools \"Bash(git diff *),Bash(git log *),Bash(git status *),Bash(git commit *)\"", "preceding_paragraph": "This example reviews staged changes and creates a commit with an appropriate message:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "06747894b922780e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#create-a-commit", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "User-invoked skills like `/commit` and built-in commands are only available in interactive mode. In `-p` mode, describe the task you want to accomplish instead."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#create-a-commit", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "create-a-commit", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Create a commit", "level": 3, "position": 7, "text": "This example reviews staged changes and creates a commit with an appropriate message:\n\nThe `--allowedTools` flag uses permission rule syntax. The trailing ` *` enables prefix matching, so `Bash(git diff *)` allows any command starting with `git diff`. The space before `*` is important: without it, `Bash(git diff*)` would also match `git diff-index`.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "0fa284676c2960c5", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#customize-the-system-prompt", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "gh pr diff \"$1\" | claude -p \\\n  --append-system-prompt \"You are a security engineer. Review for vulnerabilities.\" \\\n  --output-format json", "preceding_paragraph": "Use `--append-system-prompt` to add instructions while keeping Claude Code's default behavior. This example pipes a PR diff to Claude and instructs it to review for security vulnerabilities:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#customize-the-system-prompt", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "customize-the-system-prompt", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Customize the system prompt", "level": 3, "position": 8, "text": "Use `--append-system-prompt` to add instructions while keeping Claude Code's default behavior. This example pipes a PR diff to Claude and instructs it to review for security vulnerabilities:\n\nSee system prompt flags for more options including `--system-prompt` to fully replace the default prompt.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7d27d0f0e536cad6", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#continue-conversations", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "# First request\nclaude -p \"Review this codebase for performance issues\"\n\n# Continue the most recent conversation\nclaude -p \"Now focus on the database queries\" --continue\nclaude -p \"Generate a summary of all issues found\" --continue", "preceding_paragraph": "Use `--continue` to continue the most recent conversation, or `--resume` with a session ID to continue a specific conversation. This example runs a review, then sends follow-up prompts:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "0992f5a5783a9e02", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#continue-conversations", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "session_id=$(claude -p \"Start a review\" --output-format json | jq -r '.session_id')\nclaude -p \"Continue that review\" --resume \"$session_id\"", "preceding_paragraph": "If you're running multiple conversations, capture the session ID to resume a specific one:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#continue-conversations", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "continue-conversations", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples > Continue conversations", "level": 3, "position": 9, "text": "Use `--continue` to continue the most recent conversation, or `--resume` with a session ID to continue a specific conversation. This example runs a review, then sends follow-up prompts:\n\nIf you're running multiple conversations, capture the session ID to resume a specific one:", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md#examples", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/headless.md", "anchor": "examples", "breadcrumb": "Run Claude Code programmatically > Examples", "level": 2, "position": 3, "text": "These examples highlight common CLI patterns. For CI and other scripted calls, add `--bare` so they don't pick up whatever happens to be configured locally.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
